## Common Pitfalls

| Pitfall | Cause | Fix |
|---------|-------|-----|
| Implement without documenting | Skip business-rules | ALWAYS create business-rules first |
| Doc mixes layers | BFF rules in frontend doc | Each doc ONLY its module |
| Generic test cases | "Works correctly" | Use Given-When-Then with concrete values |
| Context overflow | Keep all inline | Save per module, use checkpoint |
| Ignore existing patterns | Don't explore before planning | Use Explore agents + Grep |
| Non-self-contained doc | References others without context | Each doc readable alone |
| Business logic in frontend | Don't validate scope | Frontends = visual. Logic → backend |
| Create API without checking existing | Don't search for reuse | Grep BEFORE creating endpoint/component |

## Enforcement Hooks

3 hooks protect the planning flow (configured in `.claude/settings.json`):

| Hook | Type | Function |
|------|------|----------|
| `planning-eval.sh` | UserPromptSubmit | Injects current phase/component before each response |
| `pre-edit.sh` | PreToolUse | Blocks writing to {{paths.devPlans}}/{{paths.testPlans}} if components pending |
| `planning-validator.sh` | PostToolUse | Validates doc quality (required sections) |

State file: `.claude/project-memory/planning-state/{feature}.json`

